<P>
 * Thomas Witty has joined Viratek Inc., the Costa Mesa drug development 
company, as director of diagnostic research.Witty's work will focus on 
developing diagnostic tests for genetic diseases. Witty was most recently with 
Biocircuits Corp. in the San Francisco Bay Area. He also worked for Sanofi, a 
French pharmaceutical company affiliated with the Pasteur Institute; Becton 
Dickinson, a medical manufacturing company, and Micromedic, the former 
diagnostic division of Rohm and Haas, later purchased by ICN Pharmaceuticals, 
Viratek's majority stockholder. 
