<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: KLINGER PLANS TO PLAY FOR ARMY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Zachary Klinger of Capistrano Valley will play football for Army next fall, 
his father, James, said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Klinger, a 6-foot-3, 248-pound lineman, was a second-team All-South Coast 
League selection as an offensive lineman last season despite missing three 
games because of a shoulder injury.He was a second-team pick as a defensive 
lineman as a junior. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Janet Evans, a two-time Olympian and current world record-holder in the 400, 
800 and 1,500-meter freestyle, will headline the Swim Meet of Champions at the 
Marguerite Aquatics Complex in Mission Viejo June 23-26. The meet will showcase 
many swimmers who will compete for spots in the 1996 Summer Olympics in 
Atlanta. Full-session tickets are $20 for adults and $5 for children. Day 
passes are $7 for adults and $2 for children. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Erasmo Ramirez, a pitcher from Saddleback High, has signed a letter of intent 
to play baseball next season at Cal State Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 Ramirez, a left-hander, should bolster a Northridge staff that was decimated 
by injury last spring. The Matadors, who finished 25-30, did not have a 
left-handed pitcher on their 1994 roster. 
</P>
<P>
 During the regular season, Ramirez was 7-2 with an earned-run average of 2.54. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bullfrogs forward Bobby McKillop sprained his right knee during practice 
Thursday and will be out for three to four weeks, the club announced. 
</P>
<P>
 McKillop, who earned playoff MVP honors last season helping the Bullfrogs win 
the Roller Hockey International title, scored one goal in the Bullfrogs' 7-1 
season-opening victory over the Los Angeles Blades Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Kerr joined the team Thursday after helping Portland of the American 
Hockey League win the Calder Cup championship. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bullfrogs play at Las Vegas Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
