<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: METROLINK OFFERING FREE TRAIN TICKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hoping to entice commuters to leave their cars behind and take the train, 
Metrolink is offering free passes from its four Ventura County stations. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the promotion, residents can call the Ventura County Transportation 
Commission to receive a pass good for four one-way trips on Metrolink. 
</P>
<P>
 The passes are good until July 15 and can be used from Simi Valley, Moorpark, 
Oxnard and Camarillo to Los Angeles and back. 
</P>
<P>
 Regular fares range from $10 to $16 for a single round-trip ticket and $144 to 
$240 for a monthly passes. 
</P>
<P>
 To get the free tickets and a complete Metrolink schedule, call 
1-800-438-1112. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
