center near the intersection of Las Posas Road and Ponderosa Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilman Stan Daily was absent from the meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 Currently housed in a cramped former bank building on Palm Drive, the city's 
police force -- contracted Ventura County sheriff's deputies -- hope to occupy 
the building sometime next spring, city officials said. J.E. MITCHELL 
