<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; PRINCIPALS REASSIGNED DUE TO 
RETIREMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two veteran Simi Valley principals will be reassigned next year to lead the 
district's largest elementary schools as part of a shake-up among 
administrators, officials said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The changes were prompted by the retirements of two principals -- Charles F. 
Bock at Berylwood elementary and Sheila Robbins at Vista Fundamental School -- 
and the decision by Hillside Junior High Principal James Stevenson to return to 
teaching. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant Supt. Susan Parks said Stevenson asked to teach special-education 
students at Royal High School after serving for several years as junior high 
principal -- a position made more difficult by recent budget cuts that 
eliminated one assistant principal at the junior high level. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a very, very demanding job and sometimes you just need a break from 
administration," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 To fill the vacant positions, district officials on Thursday named Ronda Oster 
principal of Berylwood, the district's largest elementary school, with 850 
students. Oster is currently principal at Crestview School. 
</P>
<P>
 Barbara Marino, now principal of Township elementary, was named principal of 
Vista elementary school, the district's second-largest elementary campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Terry Webb, assistant principal at Sequoia Junior High, will take over 
Hillside Junior High. 
</P>
<P>
 Other appointments include: Dee Pekrul as principal of Township elementary, 
Mary Aguilar as principal of Crestview elementary and Ann Eklund as principal 
of White Oak elementary. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
