<P>
DUCKS WON'T OFFER LOACH NEW CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Mighty Ducks will not make a contract offer to former King forward Lonnie 
Loach, who had 91 points last season for the Ducks' minor league affiliate, the 
San Diego Gulls, but appeared in only three games with the Ducks. 
</P>
<P>
 Loach was playing out the option year of his contract, and although Duck 
General Manager Jack Ferreira has until July to make an offer, he says he will 
not do so. 
</P>
<P>
 Only one of five Duck players who were playing out their options is expected 
to be offered a contract -- center Jarrod Skalde, who spent most of the season 
in San Diego but provided a spark with the Anaheim team after an injury to 
Anatoli Semenov. 
</P>
<P>
 Ferreira said he will not offer contracts to minor league forwards Trevor 
Halverson, Robin Bawa or Joel Savage. 
</P>
