<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; DODGERS; APPENDECTOMY SIDELINES GOTT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jim Gott suffered through Wednesday night's game in Miami with what he thought 
was food poisoning. But Thursday in Chicago, his conditioned worsened, and 
within a few hours he was undergoing an appendectomy at Northwestern Memorial 
Hospital.There were no complications, and he was put on the 15-day disabled 
list. He will be replaced in the bullpen by right-hander Rudy Seanez, who was 
called up from triple-A Albuquerque.  
</P>
<P>
 Gott was struggling and had been scored on in 10 of 27 games. He has a 5-2 
record with a 5.13 earned-run average and one save.  
</P>
<P>
 Seanez was originally acquired by the Dodgers before the 1992 season from the 
Cleveland Indians for Dennis Cook and Mike Christopher. A back condition 
sidelined Seanez for the season. That November, he was traded to the Colorado 
Rockies for Jody Reed. The Rockies released him in the middle of last season 
and, after playing for San Diego, he signed a Dodger minor league contract last 
winter. 
</P>
<P>
 Seanez was 2-1 with nine saves and a 5.32 ERA in 20 games at Albuquerque. He 
struck out 26 in 22 innings. MARYANN HUDSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
