<P>
BASEBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE MAJORS; DEAL FOR PADRES STILL IN WORKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Florida businessman Malcolm Glazer is negotiating to buy a portion of the San 
Diego Padres, but an investment banker said a deal isn't imminent. Paul 
Wachter, managing director of West Coast investment banking for Wertheim 
Schroder & Co., denied a report in Thursday's Times that Padres chairman and 
managing partner Tom Werner had reached a tentative agreement to sell the team 
to Glazer for $82.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're still having discussions with them, but we're not that close," Wachter 
said. "There are some real issues that are still open." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Curt Schilling will undergo arthroscopic surgery on the knee he injured doing 
rehabilitation for his injured elbow, the Philadelphia Phillies said. The 
right-handed pitcher has been on the disabled list since May 17 after 
undergoing surgery to remove a bone spur from his right elbow. Monday, after 
doing his exercises, Schilling felt something pop in his left knee and team 
physician Phillip J. Marone determined that the surgery was necessary. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Right fielder Willie McGee of the San Francisco Giants underwent surgery to 
repair a torn left Achilles' tendon and will probably miss the rest of the 
season. 
</P>
