<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP '94 / DAILY REPORT; THE SOCCER EXPERT; KEEPING POSITION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If an attack comes from left side (1), the goalkeeper moves to the right end 
of the goal box.If an attack comes from the center (2), the goalkeeper moves 
up. And when the attack comes from the right side (3), the goalkeeper slides 
over to the left end of the goal box. On corner kicks, a defender (4) is 
positioned at each post to help the goalkeeper. On penalty kicks, the keeper is 
positioned in the center of the goal and dives to whichever side he guesses the 
kick is going. He might also remain stationary. 
</P>
<P>
 Source: Times staff 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061094-0113 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 050053 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 10, 1994, Friday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 12; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
