AMERICAN LEGION ROUNDUP; COUKOS TAKES COMMAND IN SANTA CLARITA VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Coukos pitched a four-hitter and struck out four to lead Santa Clarita 
past Van Nuys West, 3-0, in an American Legion District 20 game Thursday at 
Hart High. 
</P>
<P>
 Coukos (1-0) threw 68 pitches and did not issue a walk. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Clarita (3-0) scored all of its runs in the sixth inning on a pair of 
bunt singles, a sacrifice and two Van Nuys West throwing errors. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Hanes opened the inning with a bunt single and R.J. Huish followed with 
another. 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Bland laid down a sacrifice bunt to move the runners to second and third, 
and Hanes scored on a throwing error. 
</P>
<P>
 Aaron Dean drove in Huish on a groundout and Bland scored on an error. 
</P>
<P>
 In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
