BRIEFLY: OTHER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Unions Prepare USAir Restructuring Plan: A coalition representing unionized 
workers at USAir Group Inc. expects to submit a restructuring plan to the 
troubled airline's management within two weeks.Union officials representing 
USAir pilots, flight attendants, machinists and dispatchers met in Pittsburgh 
to discuss strategy and review analyses conducted by their financial advisers. 
The proposal will include a complete financial analysis of the Virginia-based 
carrier and a plan to stem its huge losses. The coalition's actions are 
expected to be a crucial part of USAir's efforts to restore profitability as it 
battles financial losses and fierce competition from low-cost rivals. 
</P>
