<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: ORANGE COUNTY BUSINESS; AIRPORT DIRECTOR, AIRLINES 
DISCUSS RENO AIR PROPOSAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Representatives of several major airlines that serve John Wayne Airport met 
Thursday with the airport director, Jan Mittermeier, to voice their concerns 
about a proposal that would allow discount carrier Reno Air to begin service 
later this month. 
</P>
<P>
 Though some airlines are staunchly opposed to the arrangement, the meeting 
went amicably, airport spokeswoman Courtney Weircioch said.Mittermeier offered 
to meet with the representatives so that they would fully understand the 
proposal that goes before the County Board of Supervisors next week. 
</P>
<P>
 Reno Air does not currently fly from John Wayne Airport but wants to start 
operating six daily flights to San Jose now being flown by American Airlines, 
with which it has a strategic relationship. American wants to give up the 
routes because of competitive pressure from low-cost Southwest Airlines, which 
began flying from Orange County last month. 
</P>
<P>
 In the past, abandoned landing slots would be reapportioned to existing 
airlines at the airport, but Mittermeier said she favors the Reno Air proposal 
on a trial basis through September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
