ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: HUNTINGTON BEACH; SYMPHONIC BAND TO PERFORM OUTDOORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL BILLITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Golden West College's Symphonic Band will present an outdoor concert at 5:30 
p.m. Sunday in the community college's amphitheater near Gothard and Center 
streets. Admission and parking are free, and the event is open to the public. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the baton of conductor Tom Hernandez, the band will perform Broadway 
hits, movie themes, patriotic marches and selections from Disney's "Aladdin" 
and "Beauty and the Beast," said Lori Thomas, a spokeswoman for the college. 
</P>
<P>
 Audience members are encouraged to bring lawn chairs, blankets and a picnic 
dinner, Thomas added. Alcoholic beverages are prohibited. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas said the college's parking lot on Gothard Street "provides easy access 
to the Golden West College Amphitheater." The outdoor theater is in a 
bowl-shaped area, surrounded by trees and shrubs.BILL BILLITER 
</P>
