<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBBER CONFRONTS MAN AT CARPORT, TAKES VEHICLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An armed man surprised a motorist returning home Thursday afternoon, ordered 
him out of the car and then escaped in the vehicle, police said. The motorist 
was not harmed. 
</P>
<P>
 Just before 3 p.m., the 57-year-old victim pulled his 1990 Honda Accord into 
the carport area behind his apartment complex in the 15300 block of Golden West 
Street, Huntington Beach police Lt. Louis Ochoa said. 
</P>
<P>
 A man in his 20s with short blond hair, wearing a white T-shirt and dark 
baseball cap, pointed a blue steel automatic pistol at the motorist and ordered 
him out of the white, four-door vehicle, police said. The gunman then fled. 
</P>
<P>
 The vehicle's license plate is 2TCX389. Anyone with information regarding the 
theft is asked to call the Huntington Beach Police at (714) 536-5951. 
