<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SHERMAN OAKS; IMPACT OF BUDGET WILL BE DISCUSSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The impact of Mayor Richard Riordan's $4.2-million budget on residents of 
Sherman Oaks will be discussed Wednesday during a meeting sponsored by the 
Sherman Oaks Homeowners Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Cecilia Aguilera, Riordan's representative for the San Fernando Valley, will 
speak at the meeting, to be held at 8 p.m. at Union Federal Savings, 13300 
Ventura Blvd., Sherman Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
 The new budget would add 450 new police officers and provide overtime for 
existing officers. Richard H. Close, association president, said the group will 
ask Aguilera how this increase would affect the visibility of officers in the 
Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting also will focus on how the budget will improve the appearance of 
the community and make it more livable. JEFF SCHNAUFER 
</P>
</TEXT>
