<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEYWIDE FOCUS: FREEWAY CONNECTOR TO CLOSE FOR 2 NIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caltrans officials said the westbound connector road between the Foothill and 
Golden State freeways will be closed for two consecutive nights to allow 
construction work on the road. 
</P>
<P>
 Work crews will replace concrete along the roadway today and close the road 
from 8 p.m. until 9 a.m. Saturday morning, according to a statement issued by 
the agency. 
</P>
<P>
 The road also will be closed for work Saturday night through Sunday morning 
during the same time period. Detour signs will be posted to direct motorists 
around the road work. CHIP JOHNSON 
</P>
