<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LONG, HOT AND ENRICHING SUMMER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARYANN HAMMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Most parks and colleges offer summer enrichment programs for children.  
</P>
<P>
 Here's a sampling of what's available. 
</P>
<P>
 * Creative Arts Center, George Izay Park, 1100 W. Clark Ave., Burbank.Classes 
for children age 4 and older start June 27. Best bets: "Drawing and Painting" 
($23), "Kid Art" (drawing, painting, collage and clay, $8), "Hand-Building With 
Clay" ($18), "Clay" (using pottery wheel, $22). Call (818) 953-8763. 
</P>
<P>
 * Learning Tree University, 20920 Knapp St., Chatsworth. Classes for children 
6 and older start July 12. Best bets: "Acting" ($70), "Cartooning" ($73), 
"Fencing" ($80), "Horseback Riding" ($55 plus $90 stable fee), "Puppy Training" 
($75), "Animation" ($95), "Photography and Darkroom" ($85). Call (818) 
882-5599.  
</P>
<P>
 * Mission College Community Extension, 13356 Eldridge Ave., Sylmar. Classes 
for children 5 and older start June 25. Best bets: "Folklorico" (Mexican dance 
and culture, $43), "Modeling" ($39), "Piano" ($29), "Electronics" ($29), 
"Singing" ($39). Call (818) 365-5262.  
</P>
